title: Grateful Dead Live at Walter Koebel Halle on 1981-10-13
lineage: AUD > MR > DAT > CD no mic info
description: Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, They Love Each Other, CC Rider, Peggy-O, Cassidy, To Lay Me Down, Minglewood Blues, Bird Song-> Looks Like Rain-> Don't Ease Me In Cold Rain & Snow, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> The Wheel-> Sugar Magnolia-> Black Peter-> Sunshine Daydream, E: Satisfaction

reviews.review_text: Good show but.... Perhaps it's where the taper is standing, the guitars (all 3) are the lowest thing in the mix. It's still listenable. Weir says "T for California" in Minglewood since he can't say Russelsheim fast enough? TLMD is great, as always. Check out the 3 minute uptempo Dark Star sounding jam after Saint (which Brent & Bob continue after Jerry leaves). It would be ridiculous to recommend this AUD over the board, ultimately.

Rediculous Recommendation Oh, I don't know about that...You could recommend stuff like this to me and I'd bite. But then, I probably like these obscure shows more than most. The smaller the better and with less excitable reviews. Yum.

Much better than the board. Don't listen to the guy that said the board is much better--it's quite the opposite. Phil is up front (how I like it), and everyone else is mixed well. The board sounds tinny and lacking in low and mid range--the AUD makes you feel like you're there.
agreed is better then the board
MUCH Better Than The SBD This sounds full and real, some nice tunes!
